  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "My grandfather, not only was a very learned man in the Talmud, but he was, to that extent, that when there was a [NON-ENGLISH], a court case where the Jews did not want to go to the court of law, but they settled it among themselves, he was called as one of these judges.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And in spite of it, he had the patience to sit down with his grandchildren and play all kinds of games.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he also had that rare ability that he was teaching us the Talmud in such a manner that we did not realize that we are learning.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "He was telling us stories, starting from Adam and Eve.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And it-- later we realized, as we grew older, that they were actually the first introductions to our Talmud studies.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in spite of it, that he was a very religious man, he was an ardent Zionist, which in those days, among the religious Jews was a no-no.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was almost criticized among his peers, that how can an orthodox religious Jew be a Zionist?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because in Palestine in those days, they knew that the Jews were not very religious.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were not keeping Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were not eating kosher, and so on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But since 1933, especially when Hitler came to power, he had a foresight that something, something very bad could happen to the Jews.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And again, as an exception, he not only let but even encouraged one of his sons and two of his daughters to go on [NON-ENGLISH] and then to go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And all during the war, we knew that we have some connection to Palestine, even though we had no communication whatsoever with them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I'm jumping from--",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
